LAGOS – In his bid to actualize his presidential ambition under the platform of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Akwa lbom State Governor, Udom Emmanuel, on Wednesday named key officers of the Presidential Campaign Council for Udom Emmanuel Presidential Project. In a statement signed by Comrade Ini Ememobong, the Protem Director, External Communications, for the Presidential Project, Dr Gabriel Suswan, a serving Senator of the Federal Republic, a former governor of Benue state, and also a former House of Representatives is the chairman of the Campaign Council, while Col. Habibu Shuaibu (Rtd) was named the Director General. Shauibu is a former Governor of Plateau and Niger states and a former Chief of Staff to General Ibrahim Babangida. He is a founding member of the PDP and was a Governorship Aspirant in Kano state in 2011. The statement also named former Editor of the Punch, Bola Bolawole as the Campaign Spokesperson. Bola Bolawole holds a Masters’s degree in Political Science from the University of Ibadan and worked in Punch newspapers as an Editor, Chairman of the Editorial Board and Deputy Editor-in-Chief. He has 37 unbroken years of stellar journalism practice. The statement charged the trio to fully deploy their huge capacity, contacts and expertise to the achievement of Udom Emmanuel’s Presidential ambition.